<body>
    <h1>Asset Management</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<p>eZ Platform supports multiple binary file handling mechanisms by means o=
f an&nbsp;<code>IOHandler</code>&nbsp;interface. This feature is used by th=
e <span class=3D"confluence-link"> <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/BinaryFiel=
d+Field+Type">BinaryFile</a> </span>, <a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Media+F=
ield+Type"> <span class=3D"confluence-link">Media</span> </a>and <a href=3D=
"/display/DEVELOPER/Image+Field+Type"> <span class=3D"confluence-link">Imag=
e</span> </a>Field Types.</p>
<h1 id=3D"AssetManagement-NativeIOhandler">Native IO handler&nbsp;</h1>
<p>The IO API is organized around two types of handlers:</p>
<ul class=3D"task-list">
<li><code>eZ\Publish\IO\IOMetadataHandler</code>: Stores &amp; reads metada=
ta (validity, size, etc.)</li>
<li><code>eZ\Publish\IO\IOBinarydataHandler</code>: Stores &amp; reads bina=
rydata (actual contents)</li>
</ul>
<p>The IOService uses both.</p>
<h2 id=3D"AssetManagement-Configuration">Configuration</h2>
<p>IO handling can now be configured using semantic configuration. Assignin=
g the&nbsp;IO handlers to ezplatform itself is configurable per siteaccess.=
 This is the default configuration:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        default:
            io:
                metadata_handler: default
                binarydata_handler: default
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Metadata and binarydata handlers are configured in the <code>ez_io</code=
> extension. This is what the configuration looks like for the default hand=
lers. It declares a metadata handler and a binarydata handler, both labelle=
d 'default'. Both handlers are of type 'flysystem', and use the same flysys=
tem adapter, labelled 'default' as well.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ez_io:
    metadata_handlers:
        default:
            flysystem:
                adapter: default
    binarydata_handlers:
        default:
            flysystem:
                adapter: default
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"action-body flooded">
<p>The 'default' flysystem adapter's directory is based on your site settin=
gs, and will automatically be set to <code>%ezpublish_legacy.root_dir%/$var=
_dir$/$storage_dir$</code> (example: <code>/path/to/ezpublish_legacy/var/ez=
demo_site/storage</code>).</p>
<h3 id=3D"AssetManagement-Configurethepermissionsofgeneratedfiles">Configur=
e the permissions of generated files</h3>
<div class=3D"syntaxplugin">
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">V1.5</span>=
</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-siz=
e:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        default:
            io:
                permissions:=20
                    files: 0750 #default is 0644
                    directories: 0640 #default is 0755</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Both <code>files</code> and <code>directories</code> rules are optional.=
</p>
<p>Default values are 0644 for files and 0755 for directories.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"AssetManagement-ThenativeFlysystemhandler"><a class=3D"external-l=
ink" href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native_io_s=
pec/doc/specifications/io/native_io_handlers.md#the-native-flysystem-handle=
r" name=3D"user-content-the-native-flysystem-handler" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>=
The native Flysystem handler</h2>
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native_io_=
spec/doc/specifications/io/flysystem.thephpleague.com" class=3D"external-li=
nk" rel=3D"nofollow">league/flysystem</a> (along with <a href=3D"https://gi=
thub.com/1up-lab/OneupFlysystemBundle/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">FlysystemBundle</a>) is an abstract file handling library.</p>
<p>It is used as the default way to read &amp; write content binary files i=
n eZ Platform. It can use the <code>local</code> filesystem <em>(our defaul=
t configuration and <u>the one we officially&nbsp;support)</u></em>, but is=
 also able to read/write to <code>sftp</code>, <code>zip</code> or cloud fi=
lesystems <em>(<code>azure</code>, <code>rackspace</code>, <code>S3</code>)=
</em>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"AssetManagement-Handleroptions">Handler options</h3>
<h4 id=3D"AssetManagement-Adapter">Adapter</h4>
<p>The adapter is the 'driver' used by flysystem to read/write files. Adapt=
ers can be declared using <code>oneup_flysystem</code> as follows:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">oneup_flysystem:
    adapters:
        default:
            local:
                directory: "/path/to/directory"</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The way to configure other adapters can be found on the <a href=3D"https=
://github.com/1up-lab/OneupFlysystemBundle/blob/master/Resources/doc/index.=
md#step3-configure-your-filesystems" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollo=
w">bundle's online documentation</a>. Note that we do not use the Filesyste=
m configuration described in this documentation, only the adapters.</p>
<h2 id=3D"AssetManagement-TheDFSClusterhandler">The DFS Cluster handler</h2=
>
<p>For clustering use we provide a custom metadata handler that stores meta=
data about your assets in the database. This is done as it is faster then a=
ccessing the remote NFS or S3 instance in order to read metadata. For furth=
er reading on setting this up, see&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/DEVELOPER/Clust=
ering">Clustering</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>=20
</div>=20
